paragraph.content:
a product take-back scheme under which a manufacturer, importer, wholesaler
                    or retailer is required to collect certain products for proper waste
                    management;

a deposit-refund scheme under which a consumer is required to pay a deposit
                    to be refunded on the return of certain products to a specified collection
                    point;

subsection.def:
regulated article (受規管物品) means an article constituted by—(a)a product specified in column 2 of Part 2 of Schedule 8;
                        and(b)a container that is—(i)specified in column 3 of that Part opposite to the product and
                            containing that product; and(ii)airtight and sealed by machine or with the aid of a tool;
                                (Added 13 of 2016 s.
                                3)

paragraph.content:
provide for such incidental, consequential, evidential, transitional,
                    savings and supplemental provisions as are necessary or expedient for giving
                    full effect to the provisions of this Ordinance;

